<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2007-01-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Protein Microarray Technology</TITLE><BODY>Protein chips have emerged as a promising approach for a wide variety of applications including the identification of protein-protein interactions, protein-phospholipid interactions, small molecule targets, and substrates of proteins kinases. They can also be used for clinical diagnostics and monitoring disease states. This article reviews current methods in the generation and applications of protein microarrays.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>